On or before December 1 of the year of expiration, a license may be renewed for a 2-year term if the licensee:
Otherwise is entitled to be licensed;
Pays to the Commissioner the renewal fee established under § 12-904 of this subtitle;
Files with the Commissioner a surety bond renewal certificate or a new surety bond required under § 12-914 of this subtitle; and
Submits to the Commissioner a renewal application on the form that the Commissioner requires.
